===The PageRank system===
===The PageRank system===
Google's central PageRank system has been criticized, some, such as [[Daniel Brandt]], calling it "undemocratic". Common arguments are that the system is unfairly biased towards large web sites, and that the criteria for a page's importance are not subject to [[peer review]]. The system is also susceptible to manipulation and fraud through the use of dummy sites. See [[Google bomb]] and [[Spamdexing]].

=== Anti competitive practices ===
  +   +
Google removed links to multimap maps when they launched google maps. This is probably because both google maps and multimap have satellite imagery. Google also displays suggested alternatives to search terms halfway down the page. Many of these are not corrections of the spellings but suggestions of particular businesses. These are generally suppliers of the product googled.
